00:00:12.610 --> 00:00:17.190
Colin Furze built his own jet engine and puts
it on...everything.

00:00:17.190 --> 00:00:24.730
He made a jet powered snow blower, a jet powered
bicycle, drove a mobility scooter 70mph in

00:00:24.730 --> 00:00:31.359
the snow and also made a video about building
a jet engine with a drill, grinder, and toilet

00:00:31.359 --> 00:00:32.829
brush holder.

00:00:32.829 --> 00:00:37.630
His most recent video is the cake-o-matic
in which eight spoons, one cake, and a lot

00:00:37.630 --> 00:00:40.560
of power feeds him birthday cake.

00:00:40.560 --> 00:00:41.560
Sort of.

00:00:41.560 --> 00:00:43.010
Check out his YouTube channel for more.

00:00:43.010 --> 00:00:48.170
Victor Sonna creates these twisted bike sculptures
that he feels represent life's ride.

00:00:48.170 --> 00:00:53.469
He uses old parts to create them and says
that society is not defined by what we create

00:00:53.469 --> 00:00:56.560
but by what we refuse to destroy.

00:00:56.560 --> 00:01:01.820
Some models include the Guernica, The Persistence
of Memory, and Boogie Woogie.

00:01:01.820 --> 00:01:07.710
Mandy Smith uses sandpaper to transform everyday
objects into uncomfortable creations.

00:01:07.710 --> 00:01:13.470
All of these objects take on a much different
feeling once made out of sandpaper such as

00:01:13.470 --> 00:01:17.970
a slide, a bed and toilet paper.

00:01:17.970 --> 00:01:18.970
Draw it.

00:01:18.970 --> 00:01:24.049
Andreas Englund created this aging superhero
series where he chronicles the life and times

00:01:24.049 --> 00:01:25.440
of a superhero.

00:01:25.440 --> 00:01:29.820
From his young days getting caught by the
paparazzi and having a hangover, to having

00:01:29.820 --> 00:01:32.600
a baby and becoming an old man.

00:01:32.600 --> 00:01:38.229
"I Fought The Law" is a photo series by Olivia
Locher dramatizing strange state laws.

00:01:38.229 --> 00:01:43.670
For instance in Alabama it's illegal to have
an ice cream cone in your back pocket.

00:01:43.670 --> 00:01:56.950
Others include laws from Hawaii, Connecticut,
Delaware, Texas, Wisconsin, and California.

00:01:56.950 --> 00:02:00.090
And now for "The Last Supper" by Platonova
Nataliya.

00:02:00.090 --> 00:02:16.060
Illustrations of different versions of the
last supper creatively placed on notebooks.

00:02:16.060 --> 00:02:20.450
Mark Wagner created this intricate art series
using one dollar bills that plays with the

00:02:20.450 --> 00:02:23.900
concept that money is just another material.

00:02:23.900 --> 00:02:29.040
The pieces themselves are all closely related
to currency such as wealth and the division

00:02:29.040 --> 00:02:30.540
of wealth and capitalism.

